---
title: Hospitality
layout: page
description: Hospitality is another aspect of living out John  17.  In verse 24, Jesus prays to the Father about us:  “Father, I desire that those also whom you have given me be with me where I am …”  This is of course an echo of John 14:2-3, “My Father’s house has many rooms ... And if I go and prepare a place for you, I will come back and take you to be with me that you also may be where I am.”  Have you ever felt a cold welcome from someone, who is tolerating your presence but doesn’t really want you there?  Jesus is not like that!  Not only does he prepare a room for us, he actually desires us to be with him!  That is the kind of hospitality we want to offer.
---

